@@ -0,0 +1,57 @@
+# RunPod TRON GPU Pattern Search Smoke
+
+## Purpose
+
+This is the first TRON GPU search smoke for the VanitySearch adaptation.
+
+It verifies that the existing VanitySearch GPU point-walking path can launch a TRON wildcard pattern search such as:
+
+```text
+T*CDEFG
+```
+
+That pattern means:
+
+- fixed leading `T`
+- any middle characters
+- `CDEFG` as suffix 5
+
+This is not a performance benchmark.
+
+## Current Implementation
+
+- `TRON_ADDR` is a separate address type.
+- `T...` wildcard patterns select TRON search.
+- TRON pattern parsing is strict: `T*<five-char-suffix>`.
+- GPU pattern mode calls `ComputeKeysTronPattern`.
+- GPU returns the 20-byte TRON payload body.
+- CPU reconstructs the TRON Base58Check address and verifies the candidate key.
+
+The current TRON GPU pattern path uses a dedicated suffix-only rule with suffix prefilter and full Base58Check confirmation. It is intended as a bounded GPU startup and direction check before proper benchmark-only worker integration.
+
+## RunPod Build And Smoke
+
+On a short-lived CUDA-capable RunPod Pod, after applying the candidate patch:
+
+```bash
+ALLOW_RUNPOD_TRON_GPU_PATTERN_SMOKE=1 CUDA_ARCH=80 scripts/runpod_tron_gpu_pattern_search_smoke.sh
+```
+
+`timeout` exit code `124` is acceptable for this smoke if there is no crash before timeout.
+
+The default smoke pattern is `T*CDEFG`, which is the strict product-rule format. The script sets `TRON_SUPPRESS_SECRET_OUTPUT=1` before running VanitySearch so an accidental hit does not print WIF/HEX private key material.
+
+The script prints a best-effort `tron_gpu_pattern_smoke_rate` line if VanitySearch reports Mkey/s before timeout. Treat that line only as a rough startup signal. It is not the final product benchmark and does not prove average/P90 generation time.
+
+## Safety
+
+- Do not run this on `47.80.70.211`.
+- Do not treat this as a speed result.
+- Do not use customer patterns or customer data.
+- Do not rely on plaintext output for production.
+- Keep `TRON_SUPPRESS_SECRET_OUTPUT=1` enabled for any bounded smoke.
+- Production return must still be handled by the Python wrapper and age encryption.
+
+## Next Gate
+
+After this smoke compiles and runs on RunPod, add a dedicated benchmark-only mode that reports complete TRON address attempts per second without ever printing private key material.
